<paragraph blockId="34.[192,1440,675,764]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,743,675,699]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Identification, taxonomy, and variation.</emphasis>
Considered one of the palest 
<emphasis box="[1096,1332,675,699]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1223,675,699]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantis">S. atlantis</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName box="[1232,1332,675,699]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesperis">hesperis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
forms, it is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moeck" authorityYear="1950" box="[343,624,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="greyi">
<emphasis box="[343,624,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria hesperis greyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[661,760,707,731]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Nevada</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1981" box="[769,1117,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="ratonensis">
<emphasis box="[769,1117,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria hesperis ratonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always has silver spots on the ventral hindwings. Adult wingspan ranges from 
<quantity box="[827,952,739,763]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="52.5" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="50.0">50-55 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[192,925,803,827]" box="[192,925,803,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,287,803,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Range.</emphasis>
Limited to Raton Mesa in northeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[770,921,803,827]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[192,1441,867,987]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,364,867,891]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Life history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1981" box="[372,725,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="ratonensis">
<emphasis box="[372,725,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria hesperis ratonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be a Pleistocene relict related to prairie dwelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="dos Passos and Grey" authorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="helena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S. hesperis helena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[411,506,899,923]" name="Canada" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Canada</collectingCountry>
(Scott 1981). The two populations likely inhabited mixed grassland and aspen forests on the southern plains. When the climate warmed, 
<emphasis box="[940,990,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S. h</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1089,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helena">
<emphasis box="[1008,1089,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">helena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
advanced north while 
<emphasis box="[1381,1432,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S. h</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[192,319,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">ratonensis</emphasis>
move up in elevation.
</paragraph>
